    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras face a challenging slate today, exacerbated by the unfortunate rainouts of core power bats **Yordan Alvarez**, **Trea Turner**, and **Kyle Schwarber**. In their absence, **Pete Crow-Armstrong** anchors the lineup with the day\u2019s highest efficiency score of 76.26. His matchup against the struggling Waldron (7.83 xERA) provides a massive +19% SP Skill boost, and his dynamic platoon advantage makes him a must-start despite the lower order placement. **Junior Caminero** also projects as an elite play (74.22), benefiting significantly from a premium #2 spot in the order and a favorable platoon matchup against Williams, G. These two provide the necessary ceiling in a day where high-end production is thin due to the weather-induced benching of our heavy hitters.\n\n**Kazuma Okamoto** (61.18) and **Hyeseong Kim** (61.99) represent our next tier of strong starts. **Hyeseong Kim** is particularly interesting today; while he occupies the #7 slot, the combination of a solid matchup against Alcantara, S and a wind-out advantage pushes his projection into the strong category. Conversely, **Colt Keith** (46.51) remains in the lineup only out of necessity. Facing a legitimate ace in Ritchie (2.08 xERA), **Colt Keith** suffers a -19% SP Skill penalty, making him a marginal play at best. The most difficult bench decision involved **Dillon Dingler** (33.16); while his raw projections were tempting, the steep penalty against a high-tier arm like Ritchie kept him well below our 40-point \"Below Floor\" threshold, signaling a day to preserve games against tough competition.",
